意大利“零号病人”或在德国感染。
Italy "patient zero" or infection in Germany.
澎湃新闻                      。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
有内涵的时政新媒体。
Connotation of the new political media.
澎湃新闻记者 南博一3月11日，有外媒报道称，意大利米兰的一个研究团队认为，意大利的新冠肺炎疫情可能是经德国传播，而非直接来自中国。
NEW YORK (Reuters) - A research team in Milan, Italy, has suggested that the outbreak of pneumonia in Italy could have been spread through Germany rather than directly from China, media reported Monday.
因为有研究表明，目前意大利较早出现的新冠病毒毒株的基因测序与一例1月在德国出现的病例的病毒毒株基因测序相匹配。
Because research has shown that gene sequencing of the earlier Italian strain of the new crown virus matches that of a virus strain that appeared in Germany in January.
据路透社3月11日报道，自从2月21日在意大利北部伦巴第大区首次发现新冠肺炎病例以来，科学家一直在寻找意大利的“零号患者”。
Scientists have been searching for Italian sufferer No.1 since the first case of pneumonia was reported in northern Italy's Lombardy region on February 21.
米兰的研究团队虽然尚未完全确定”零号病人”，但通过对较早期新冠病毒的基因测序发现，该病毒与一个1月出现在德国的病例的新冠病毒基因序列相匹配。
The Milan team has not yet fully identified "patient zero," but genetic sequencing of the earlier canopy virus has shown that it matches the sequence of a new crown virus in a case that appeared in Germany in January.
“最接近于意大利一个较早期病毒的基因序列，来自于一个大约在1月19日至1月22日之间在德国慕尼黑感染的病例，”米兰萨科医院传染病科研究小组负责人马西莫·加利（Massimo Galli）表示。
"The gene sequence closest to an earlier virus in Italy came from a case of infection in Munich, Germany, between about January 19 and January 22," said Massimo Galli, director of the infectious diseases team at Mirasaco Hospital.
上述被检测的较早期病毒被认为可能是意大利所有病毒的“祖先”。
The older virus tested is thought to be the "ancestor" of all Italian viruses.
加利还补充道，这名德国患者是在与一名来自中国的人员有过接触后感染了病毒。
Gali also added that the German patient was infected with the virus after contact with a person from China.
加利表示，他所在研究团队的分析表明，新冠肺炎疫情早在1月25日至26日就已经在意大利出现，这比北部城市科多诺（Codogno）正式诊断出意大利境内首例患者的时间要早很多。
Galli said his team's analysis showed that the outbreak had already occurred in Italy from January 25 to 26, much earlier than the northern city of Codogno had officially diagnosed the first case in Italy.
“我们可以想象，一个人（“零号病人”）在慕尼黑接触了已经感染的人，然后又到了意大利，这个人‘没有任何症状’地将病毒在意大利传播开了。
"We can imagine a person (" patient zero ") contacting infected people in Munich and then Italy, where he spread the virus' without any symptoms'.
”加利说道。
"said Gali.
意大利医生们最初认为科多诺出现的首例病患是被一位从中国返回的同事传染，但后来这位同事的检测结果为阴性，这表明这个从中国返回的人并不是“零号病人”。
Doctors in Italy initially thought the first case of Cordono had been infected by a colleague returning from China, but the colleague tested negative, suggesting that the man returning from China was not a "zero patient."
